  "instruction": "Write a Common Lisp macro `with-saved-place` that snapshots a place's current value, executes body, and restores the place to the snapshotted value when body unwinds (normally or via non-local exit). Use a gensym to hold the saved value.",
  "reference_defmacro": "(defmacro with-saved-place (place &body body)\n  (let ((g (gensym)))\n    `(let ((,g ,place))\n       (unwind-protect (progn ,@body)\n         (setf ,place ,g)))))",
